          <h3>Inspiration</h3>
          <p>
            I spend my work time working with systems that analyze
            emails. The quality of results of the statistical, text
            analytics and machine learning work is quite dependent on
            the input data, and I was getting tired of hacking emails
            from the <a href="https://www.cs.cmu.edu/~./enron/"> Enron
              corpus</a> into the shape I wanted. At first I was just
            creating email addresses with real-looking names, but it
            quickly spread into text generation using Markov. It's a
            fun toy.
          </p>

          <h3>Contact</h3>
          <p>
            If you like this, or if you hate it, I'd love to hear
            from you. Drop me a line:
            <br><span class="fa fa-twitter"></span>
            <a href="https://twitter.com/iantruslove">@iantruslove</a>
            <br><span class="fa fa-envelope-o"></span> first dot last
            at gmail dot com.
          </p>

